{{Infobox news event | title = 2008 Kazan gas explosion | image = [[File:Tatarstan in Russia.svg|250px]] | caption = Location of Tatarstan in Russia | date = 9 January 2008 | place = Kazan, Tatarstan, Russia | cause = gaz explosion | reported injuries = 4 | reported death(s) = 10 }}
The '''[[Kazan]] gas explosion''' occurred on January 9, 2008, destroying an entire corner of a three-story [[khrushchyovka]]-style apartment building on Malaya Pechyorskaya Street in the [[Aviastroitelny District]] of [[Kazan]], [[Tatarstan]], [[Russia]]. The explosion took place at 0:28&nbsp;a.m. local time ([[UTC]] +3).
The blast destroyed 12 apartments and killed ten residents, including one woman who died of blast-related trauma in a [[hospital]] after being rescued from the rubble. Additionally, two were non-fatally wounded.
Rescue efforts were complicated by low temperatures of -30&nbsp;°C, raising concerns that victims trapped in the destroyed building might freeze before being reached by rescuers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://rt.com/news/apartment-blast-kills-eight-in-kazan/|title=Apartment blast kills eight people in Kazan|publisher=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=9 January 2008|accessdate=6 November 2015}}</ref>
Three of the building residents, including one child, were not immediately accounted for. However, several body parts were found in the ruins,<ref>[http://gzt.ru/incident/2008/01/14/194250.html В Казани в развалинах взорвавшегося дома найдены фрагменты останков тел] {{ru icon}}</ref> and subsequent DNA analyses determined that the young girl and her grandfather were both among those killed in the explosion. The girl's grandmother, also thought to have been in the apartment, is still counted missing.<ref name="followup">{{Cite web | last = Басилая | first = Вера | script-title=ru:Опознаны останки семьи, считавшейся пропавшей при взрыве газа в Казани | work = [[Komsomolskaya Pravda]] | accessdate = 2008-09-30 | date = 2008-02-27 | url = http://www.kp.ru/daily/24055/300905/ |language=ru}}</ref>
The exact cause of the blast has not been established. While a criminal investigation was initiated, city authorities suspect that the cause may have been improper use of gas appliances.<ref>[http://www.kp.ru/daily/24031/94152 Из-за взрыва в квартире №13 погиб человек], ''[[Komsomolskaya Pravda]]'' {{ru icon}}</ref>
The Kazan city government arranged for residents of the building destroyed in the blast to receive apartments in newly constructed buildings. On July 10, 2008, the first nine affected families received keys to new apartments in a building on [[Fatix Amirxan|Amirkhan]] Street. The residents received the apartments in exchange for their destroyed ones, an arrangement set up by the city-held ''[[Open joint-stock company|OAO]] Residential Investment Company of the City of Kazan'' and supported by Kazan mayor [[Ilsur Metshin]] and the district administration. Families were also given the opportunity to pay for larger apartments at a discounted price per square meter.<ref name="recpt">[http://www.gik-kazan.ru/index.php?p=05_02_20080710000000 "Жители дома, пострадавшего от взрыва бытового газа, обрели новые квартиры."] (July 10, 2008) ''Жилишная инвестиционная компания г.Казани''</ref>
