'''Ecopower''' is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[cooperative]] founded in 1991, financing [[renewable energy]] projects in [[Flanders]]. Since the liberalisation of the energy market in Flanders (July 2003) Ecopower became a supplier of green electricity produced in Belgium. At the end of 2010 1% of the Flemish households were supplied by Ecopower.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.standaard.be/Artikel/Detail.aspx?artikelId=G4IVNI6G|title=DE NIEUWE ENERGIEMAKERS (1). Albertkanaal is de toekomst|author=(pse)|work=De Standaard}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ec.europa.eu/energy/idae_site/deploy/prj044/prj044_1.html|title=I D A E - ECOPOWER brings together Flemish citizens to invest in renewable energy|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.liberation.fr/terre/0101120719-en-belgique-la-petite-ecopower-turbine-fort|title=En Belgique, la petite Ecopower turbine fort|work=liberation.fr}}</ref> Projects in recent years include the placement of [[wind turbines]] in [[Eeklo]], [[Gistel]] and [[Ghent]], and the placement of [[water turbine|hydroelectric turbine]]s in [[Rotselaar]], [[Hoegaarden]] and [[Overijse]].<ref>{{Official|http://www.ecopower.be}}</ref>

Ecopower is member of the [[Belgium]] group of renewable cooperatives [[REScoop.be]] and the European group of renewable cooperatives [[REScoop.eu]].

