{{Infobox company | name = Melhus Energi | logo = | fate = [[Merger]] | successor = [[TrønderEnergi]] | foundation = | defunct = 2001 | location = [[Melhus]], [[Norway]] | industry = [[Power company|Power]] | key_people = | products = [[Hydroelectricity]] | num_employees = | parent = [[Melhus|Municipality of Melhus]] | subsid = }}
'''Melhus Energi''' is a defunct [[power company]] that operated [[hydroelectricity|hydro electric power plants]] and the [[power grid]] in [[Melhus]], [[Norway]]. Until it merged with [[TrønderEnergi]] in 2001 it was owned entirely by the [[municipalities of Norway|municipality]] of [[Melhus]].
